CEO Strategic Review — Trak Football Pilot Wedge
Scoring Matrix
Dimension	Score	Reasoning
Market Fit	2/5	Q1 demand is triangulated from coaches asking + founder living the pain + indirect "players use Notes/Instagram" evidence. Zero named players have described the pain in their own words — and the product positions as player-first. Q2 cost (€500/year × 500–800 TAM) is real but parent-side; the player-side demand thesis is explicitly an assumption the Q4 metric is designed to test. That is the textbook definition of "we think users want this."
